Tragopogon porrifolius

   [2442.gif]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Asterales:Compositae
   Synonyms
   Common names salsify, oyster plant, vegetable oyster, purple
   goat's-beard, cercefi roxo, barba de bode
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2442

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: A herbaceous plant reaching up to 1 m in height. Its long,
   slender, pointed, smooth, flat leaves are about 2.5 cm in width at the
   crown and are 25-30 cm long. Roots are 20-30 cm long, cylindrical, 2.5
   cm or less in diameter, and salmon or brown in colour. Older roots
   possess a white, milky white sap. It produces purple to lilac flowers
   in the second year. USE: It is used in soups and stews; it can be
   boiled, cut into small pieces, and creamed like asparagus. It can be
   cut into long strips, boiled, and then fried in butter or mashed.
   GROWING PERIOD: Cool-season biennial herb. It is grown as an annual
   with culture similar to that for parsnips or carrots. It requires a
   long growing season of 120 to 150 days from seeding to harvest. COMMON
   NAMES: Salsify, Oyster-plant, Vegetable oyster. FURTHER INF: In
   semiarid regions, salsify requires irrigation. Rocky, shallow, or heavy
   clay soils tend to produce mis-shaped roots.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Hartmann T 1981 pp 585 [DEP, DRA, FER, TEXT]
   Duke J 1975 pp 29 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 469 [USE]

